<h2>Log a risk</h2>

<p>Risks are potential issues that could impact your project. To log a risk:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Go to the project details page</li>
    <li>Click on the <strong>Risks</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Add risk</strong> button</li>
    <li>Fill in the risk details:
        <ul>
            <li>Title (required) - A brief description of the risk</li>
            <li>Description (required) - Detailed explanation of the risk</li>
            <li>Risk type (optional) - Category of the risk</li>
            <li>Probability (required) - How likely the risk is to occur</li>
            <li>Impact (required) - The severity if the risk materialises</li>
            <li>Mitigation plan (optional) - Steps to reduce or eliminate the risk</li>
            <li>Status (required) - Current status of the risk</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create</strong> to save the risk</li>
</ol>

<h3>Best practice</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Log risks early - don't wait until they become issues</li>
    <li>Be specific about the risk and its potential impact</li>
    <li>Update mitigation plans as you work through risks</li>
    <li>Review and update risk status regularly</li>
    <li>Close risks when they are no longer relevant or have been fully mitigated</li>
</ul>

